  "model": "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
  "response_text": "# Jain-Compliant Vegetable Curry\n\n## Ingredients\n- 2 tbsp ghee or oil\n- 1 tsp cumin seeds\n- 1 tsp mustard seeds\n- 2-3 green chiles, slit lengthwise\n- 1 tbsp ginger, finely minced\n- 2 cups cauliflower florets\n- 2 cups green beans, cut into 2-inch pieces\n- 1 cup bell peppers (any color), diced\n- 1 cup tomatoes, diced (or 1/2 cup tomato puree)\n- 1 cup peas (fresh or frozen)\n- 1 cup coconut milk (or yogurt)\n- 1 tsp cumin powder\n- 1/2 tsp turmeric\n- 1/2 tsp coriander powder\n- Salt to taste\n- Fresh cilantro for garnish\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. **Temper the spices**: Heat ghee in a large pan. Add cumin and mustard seeds; let them crackle (30 seconds).\n\n2. **Add aromatics**: Add slit green chiles and ginger. Stir for 1 minute.\n\n3. **Cook vegetables**: Add cauliflower and green beans. Stir-fry for 3-4 minutes.\n\n4. **Build the curry**: Add bell peppers and tomatoes. Cook for 2 minutes.\n\n5. **Season**: Sprinkle cumin powder, turmeric, and coriander. Mix well.\n\n6. **Simmer**: Add coconut milk and peas. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 10-12 minutes until vegetables are tender.\n\n7. **Finish**: Adjust salt and garnish with cilantro.\n\n**Serves 4 | Ready in 25 minutes**",
